<F P=100> BENELUX </F>
<F P=101> Netherlands </F>
<H3> <TI>   Legislature Urges Trial of FRY Politicians, Commanders </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0403171094 Hilversum Radio Netherlands in English 1130 GMT 
4 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0403171094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Dutch parliament wants politicians and military 
commanders in former Yugoslavia to stand trial at the 
International Court of Justice in The Hague for their share in 
setting up concentration camps. So far there's been only talk 
of prosecuting low-ranking army officials for such war crimes. 
  Some members of Dutch parliament claim that the worst 
criminals in former Yugoslavia are not those wearing uniforms 
but those who put on suits to attend peace negotiations. The 
special tribunal at the International Court of Justice in The 
Hague is to start conducting its first trials this year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

