<H3> <TI>   * Government Presents Economic Stimulus Program </TI></H3>
<H4>   * Large Drop in Local Government Jobs </H4>
<F P=102> 94EN0221F Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT in Finnish 2 Feb 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> 94EN0221F </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Unemployment of Local Government </F>
Employees Rose 55 Percent"] 
  [Text] The number of local government employees receiving 
unemployment benefits rose 55 percent during the year. The 
unemployment fund of the local government employees' trade union 
KTV paid unemployment benefits to over 77,000 of its members. 
The union has about 230,000 members in all. 
  The KTV fund paid about 1.5 billion markkas in benefits last 
year. Sixty percent of the recipients were completely 
unemployed. Benefits were paid for 139 days on the average. 
Women made up 72 percent of the benefit recipients. 
  Nearly 3,000 local government employees lost benefits tied 
to 
earnings because their unemployment lasted over 500 days. 

</TEXT>

