<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Special Coordinator Lamb Arrives, Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0703172594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1600 GMT 7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0703172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Robert Lamb, U.S. special coordinator on the Cyprus 
issue, said that he has positive expectations for the talks and 
does not expect to face any problems. Speaking upon his arrival 
in Cyprus this afternoon, Mr. Lamb added that Washington 
believes the proximity talks on the confidence-building measures 
[CBM's] are proceeding well. He noted: There are difficulties 
and serious questions that, however, are addressed 
constructively and with prudence. 
  The U.S. coordinator also said that he comes to Cyprus to be 
informed of the precise positions of the two sides, and that the 
United States believes this is a very critical time for the 
Cyprus issue and the future of Cyprus. Mr. Lamb added: What is 
going on now could open opportunities for the solution of 
problems that have been causing hardship for the island for a 
long time. Mr. Lamb further noted that the United States is 
prepared to offer any help it can. 
  Asked about his recent visit to Moscow, Mr. Lamb said that a 
series of problems, including the Cyprus issue, were discussed 
during his visit. 

</TEXT>

