Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] In a statement to Europe No. 1 Radio today, 
European Commission President Jacques Delors unleashed a harsh 
attack against our country and stressed that Greece should be 
careful of the measures it has taken against the small republic 
of Macedonia [The Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM], 
as he called Skopje, and added that these measures are not 
acceptable. [passage omitted] 
  Responding to Delors statement, government spokesman 
Evangelos Venizelos said: Mr. Delors has made a very general 
