concept of European solidarity, to which Greece also attaches 
very great importance. Mr. Delors has his views on the measures 
the Greek Government took on 16 February and he outlined these 
as president of the Commission in the letter he sent to the 
prime minister; the replies and procedures are well known. Mr. 
Venizelos concluded: Nothing special emerged in today's radio 
statement by Mr. Delors. 

