<F P=101> Inter-European Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Belgium's Claes Rebukes Spain, Portugal on Expansion </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0903123994 Brussels BELGA in French 2218 GMT 8 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0903123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed LVE: "Expansion: Claes Criticizes Spanish </F>
and Portuguese Intransigence"; as released by Brussels BELGA 
Database] 
  [Text] Brussels, 8 Mar (BELGA) -- Belgian Foreign Minister 
Willy Claes harshly criticized Spanish and Portuguese 
intransigence Tuesday [9 March] evening regarding the issue of 
fisheries, calling on these two countries to moderate their 
demands regarding access by their trawlers to Norwegian waters. 
  "Certain member states want to transform the European Union 
(EU) into a fish shop," he stated on the BRTN [Dutch-language 
Belgian Radio and Television]. According to him, tough words 
were expressed within the Council toward these two countries. 
"Too much is too much," he said, feeling that the demands made 
by these two countries is excessive. 
  Mr. Claes used the financial argument: "Spain and Portugal 
would be well-advised to take account of the fact that Norway 
will be a net contributor to the Community budget, with all the 
benefits which that implies for the four cohesion countries 
(Spain, Portugal, Greece, and Ireland -- editor's note)," he 
said. 
  The Belgian foreign minister added that Oslo had already 
taken two steps toward the EU: The first during its accession 
to the European Economic Area, the free-trade agreement between 
the EC and the EFTA countries (except Switzerland, which voted 
against it) which stipulates that the countries receiving 
cohesion funds should receive an extra fishing quota of 11,000 
tonnes of cod in Norwegian waters, and the second during the 
negotiations of recent days, during which "appreciable steps" 
have been taken. 
  Mr. Claes added that, nevertheless, he was still "confident" 
about the chances of unravelling this Gordian knot "this very 
night." 

</TEXT>

