<H3> <TI>   Kinkel `Optimistic' About EU Agreement With Norway </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903121794 Hamburg DPA in German 1125 GMT 9 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0903121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- After the temporary failure of the 
European Union's [EU] membership negotiations with Norway, FRG 
Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel (Free Democratic Party) is 
optimistic that an agreement can still be reached. "We must not 
give up now but continue to negotiate," he said in Bonn on 
Wednesday [9 February]. The remaining problems can be overcome 
and can be solved. The continuing negotiations should link up 
with a new meeting of the European Union's Council of Ministers 
on 15 March. 

