<H3> <TI>   SPD Official Calls Talks With Norway `Disgrace' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903121594 Hamburg DPA in German 1047 GMT 9 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0903121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The Social Democratic Party [SPD] 
calls the failure of the membership negotiations with Norway a 
"disgrace" for the governments of the European Union. The 
inflexible attitude by Spain and Britain toward Norway calls the 
already concluded agreements with Austria, Finland, and Sweden 
into question again, Deputy SPD Chairwoman Heidi Wieczorek-Zeul 
said in Bonn on Wednesday. The negotiations in Brussels have 
shown how necessary a reform of the Europan institutions is "at 
the head and at the limbs," if an expanded European Union wants 
to remain capable of acting. 

</TEXT>

