<H3> <TI>   Rexrodt Urges Continued Modest Wage Settlements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0803130294 Hamburg DPA in German 1140 GMT 8 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0803130294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Economics Minister Guenter Rexrodt (Free Democratic 
Party) has said that the figures published by the Federal 
Statistical Office have confirmed the government's economic 
expectations. It is now "more than mere hope" that housing 
construction and exports will contribute to a recovery of the 
economy. A decline of the inflation rate below 3 percent in the 
course of the year is also "within reach." Rexrodt demanded 
that the "path of moderate wage settlements and of the 
consolidation of the budget should be continued." This would 
make possible further interest rate reductions. 

