<H3> <TI>   January Trade Balance, Exports Viewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0703135294 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1226 GMT 5 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0703135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Italy's Trade Balance in Red Outside </F>
European Union"] 
  [Text] Rome, 5 Mar (ANSA) -- Italy's trade balance with 
countries outside the European Union dipped into the red in 
January, a month which is traditionally bad for Italian trade, 
while over all exports rose 13.1 percent against a 4.5 percent 
increase in imports, according to the national statistics bureau 
ISTAT [Central Statistics Institute]. 
  Last January, Italian exports outside the European Union 
totaled 8.864 trillion lire (5.26 million dollars), while 
imports were valued at 9.056 trillion lire (5.374 billion 
dollars). 
  On a sector-by-sector basis, transport means showed the 
worst 
performance with a 34-percent plunge in exports. ISTAT noted, 
however, that by excluding ship sales there was actually a 19 
percent increase in sale abroad. 
  The following table, expressed in billion European lira, 
with 
one dollar worth 1,685 lire Friday [4 March], compares Italy's 
exports to various areas of the world in 1993 and 1994: 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|                         |1993                     |1994                     | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|European Free Trade Agre-|- 199                    |- 306                    | 
|ement area               |                         |                         | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Central and East Europe  |- 251                    |- 261                    | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|OPEC                     |- 497                    |- 547                    | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|United States            |+ 79                     |+ 464                    | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|China                    |- 156                    |- 204                    | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Japan                    |- 225                    |- 114                    | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Singapore, Korea, Taiwan,|+ 138                    |+ 363                    | 
| Hong Kong               |                         |                         | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
|Others                   |+ 282                    |+ 413                    | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 



