Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Thorough Investigation at the </F>
Faeroes"] 
  [Text] Within the next few days the Danish Government and 
the Faeroese provincial government will jointly institute a 
committee that will be charged with elucidating the social 
economic transactions of the Faeroe Islands in the 1980's. 
  The committee's work will conclude with a report also 
containing a thorough examination of the administrative 
decisions made by the Faeroese banks in the 1980's that 
contributed to the bankruptcy of the two largest Faeroese banks. 
  The provincial government wants the committee to be 
appointed 
by 1 February so that the report can be finished by 1 July. 
According to a statement from the Faeroese Representative 
Council, the committee's members must all be independent from, 
among other things, the Faeroese banks, the National Bank, the 
Danish Bank, and the Financial Inspectorate. 

</TEXT>

