<H3> <TI>   French Official Arrives for Multinational Force Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0903095594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0930 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0903095594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Mar. 9 (A.A.) -- Denis Bauchard, French 
foreign minister for North Africa and Middle East affairs [name 
and title as received], arrived in Ankara on Tuesday [8 March] 
for the four-way multinational force meeting. 
  Officials at the French Embassy welcomed Bauchard at 
Esenboga 
Airport outside Ankara. 
  Turkey, the United States, Britain, and France will hold a 
four-way meeting on March 10 and review the activities of 
multinational force that was set up to protect Kurds living in 
northern Iraq. 
  Operation Provide Comfort was in place to protect Iraqi 
Kurds 
fleeing the attacks of Saddam Husayn and involved 21,700 troops 
at its peak on May 21, 1991. 
  After extending the mandate of the multinational force in 
December Turkey proposed to review the matter in a four-way 
meeting. The ground troops of the force have been withdrawn and 
only an air force remains in the region. 

</TEXT>

