<H3> <TI>   Mentese Announces Measures To Safeguard Voters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0803153594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1435 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0803153594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Mar. 8 (A.A.) -- Interior Minister Nahit 
Mentese said today that all kinds of measures have been taken 
for the March 27 local elections and any behavior aimed at 
restricting freedom of choice during the elections, will be 
neutralized immediately. 
  In a written statement on measures taken by the government 
to 
provide security during the polls, Mentese said it was an 
important duty of the state to enable citizens to vote in a 
secure atmosphere. 
  He added that any incident occurring in any part of the 
country will immediately be forwarded to a "crisis desk" to be 
formed in the ministry, which will take relevant measures. 
  "The security measures will enable the elections to reflect 
the free will of people," he said. 

