<H3> <TI>   Forty-Five `Terrorists' Captured in Istanbul </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0803154294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1430 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0803154294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul, Mar. 8 (A.A.) -- Fourty-five terrorists 
from an outlawed separatist organization were caught during a 
series of operations, it was reported on Tuesday [8 March]. 
  Istanbul anti-terrorism officials said security forces, 
acting on a tip, staged operations against the terror 
organization and caught the terrorists who are believed 
responsible for various offenses including bomb and firebomb 
attacks, setting several state and private buildings on fire and 
killings. 
  Eight weapons, one hand grenade and a large quantity of 
ammunition were seized in safe houses belonging to the 
terrorists. 
  An investigation has been launched into the incident. 

</TEXT>

