<H3> <TI>   Italy To Appoint CSCE Mediators in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0803122894 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1120 GMT 
8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0803122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Italy will have to select and appoint ombudsmen 
(mediators) for Bosnia in its capacity as the current president 
of the Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe. 
  The decision was made by the executive committee of the 
CSCE. 
  The mediators will be entrusted with the task of promoting 
respect for human and minority rights. Their mandate envisages, 
among other things, the reestablishment of CSCE observation 
missions in the regions of Kosovo, Vojvodina, and Sandzak. 

