<H3> <TI>   Italy Urges Russian Participation in July G-7 Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0703163494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1302 GMT 
7 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0703163494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Italy, which currently chairs the G-7, is pressing 
for Russia to be allowed to take part in the G-7 meeting to be 
held in Naples from 8 to 10 July. The meeting, unlike past 
ones, will place a greater emphasis on political themes. The 
news was revealed by Prime Minister Carlo Azeglio Ciampi who 
unveiled the G-7 logo in Naples today. 
  Ciampi stressed that there is no reason to believe that 
there 
will be Russian participation at the heart of G-7. He also made 
it clear that there has been no UN request for Italy to take 
part in operations in Bosnia. 

