<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Papoulias `Satisfied' After Meeting Delors </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0803142094 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1230 GMT 8 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0803142094 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos described 
the meeting between Greek Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias and 
European Union [EU] Commission President Jacques Delors as 
particularly positive. Venizelos stated that Papoulias said he 
was satisfied with the meeting and hoped it would produce 
results. Responding to a question on whether there is a new 
initiative from Delors on the issue of Skopje, the spokesman 
said that for several days there has been a political initiative 
from the EU Commission that could take more specific forms. 
Venizelos said that anything that leads to the formulation of 
positions for the resumption of the dialogue is positive. 
  The government spokesman also said that Foreign Minister 
Papoulias, who is presiding over the EU Council of Ministers, 
will visit Belgrade and Moscow. However, the dates of his 
visits were not revealed. Referring to the purpose of the 
visits, the spokesman said that it is obvious: To be informed 
in person on the positions of the Serb leadership and the 
Russian initiatives in the Balkans. 

</TEXT>

