<F P=100> INTER-EUROPEAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Veto of Norway's Membership To Continue </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903180594 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1700 GMT 
9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Spain will continue vetoing Norway's entry into the 
EU if Norway no longer permits fishing in its territorial 
waters. This is the firm stance adopted by Foreign Minister 
Javier Solana, who today met his Portuguese counterpart Jose 
Durao Barroso, who has emphasized his support for Spain in this 
area. 
  Solana also referred to yesterday's attack on a Spanish 
airplane while flying on a United Nations mission. The attack 
took place over Krajina, an area controlled by the Serbs. 
Solana described the attack as very serious, and said that it 
is up to the international community to respond because this is 
the first time that a UN plane has been attacked. 

</TEXT>

