<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Inter-European Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Havel Remains Cautious on EU Membership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1003103494 Brussels EUROPE in English 8 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1003103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels EUROPE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Czech Republic: Mr. Havel Says His </F>
Country Is Waiting To Be `Ripe' for Membership"; as released by 
Brussels TEXTLINE database] 
  [Text] The speed with which the Czech Republic can become a 
member of the European Union [EU] will depend partly on how 
quickly changes take place in the country, but also on the 
Union's strategy for future enlargement. President Havel made 
this comment at a press conference, adding that conditions for 
membership have become more stringent following the Community's 
"metamorphosis" into a Union. "We cannot apply for membership 
tomorrow or the next day.... We are waiting to be ripe," he 
added. Mr. Havel did not express a view on the advisability of 
"partial" membership (to the second and third pillars, for 
example) but underscored his country's will to participate in 
political dialogue with the EU. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

