<H3> <TI>   Kinkel Regrets Failure of EU Fishing `Breakthrough' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903163294 Hamburg DPA in German 1442 GMT 9 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0903163294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn -- FRG Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel (Free 
Democratic Party of Germany) gave assurances at a news 
conference that the foreign ministers of the European Union [EU] 
will meet again next Tuesday [15 March], because "we do not give 
up so quickly." Kinkel regretted that the breakthrough "in the 
vexatious fishing issue" has failed because of Spain. It is not 
justified to speak of a crisis, even in view of the differences 
of opinion with Great Britain concerning the majorities in a 
16-member EU. Kinkel appealed to the European Parliament in 
Strasbourg not to let the procedure for membership fail because 
of the pressure of time before the new elections. He is 
convinced that the negotiations with Norway will be concluded 
successfully. 

