<H3> <TI>   Duesseldorf Wants To Cancel Deportation of Refugees </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0903142194 Hamburg DPA in German 1035 GMT 9 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0903142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Duesseldorf (DPA) -- The North Rhine-Westphalian 
Interior Ministry wants to cancel the first flight deporting 
refugees to Serbia, which is planned for this Thursday [10 
March], if the FRG Interior Ministry is not able to clarify 
whether agreements concluded with the Romanian authorities are 
still valid. The ministry announced this in Duesseldorf in 
Wednesday. 
  On Thursday, about 100 refugees from what remains of 
Yugoslavia are to be flown from Duesseldorf to the Romanian 
border airport of Timisoara, and then taken by bus to the 
Serbian border. Three additional special flights have been 
agreed on with the Romanian state airline Tarom for this month. 
About 500 asylum-seekers, illegal immigrants, criminals, and 
refugees with expired residence permits are to be deported from 
North Rhine-Westphalia to Serbia. 

</TEXT>

