<H3> <TI>   Sextant Avionique To Equip Russian MiG Trainer Aircraft </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR0803125094 Brussels EUROPEAN REPORT in English 2 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0803125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels EUROPEAN REPORT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Sextant (Thomson CSF) To Fit </F>
Electronics to MiG"; as released by Brussels Euroscope EIS 
Database] 
  [Text] Sextant Avionique, a subsidiary of Thomson CSF, the 
French state-owned electronics and defence procurement group, 
has been awarded a contract by Mikoyan, the manufacturer of the 
MiG fighter aircraft. The contract covers the supply of onboard 
controls for the MiG AT trainer aircraft. 
  The engines for the MiG AT are supplied by SNECMA, the 
French 
aircraft engine supplier. Sextant is supplying its Topflight 
electronic system which will be fitted to the aircraft with the 
assistance of the Russian group, Gosnias. The first prototype 
of the MiG AT is expected to take to the air in 1995. The 
potential market for such a trainer aircraft is estimated at 
between 600 and 1,200, of which 500 are for Russia alone. 

</TEXT>

