<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian Envoy, Industry Minister Discuss Economic Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903203794 Tehran IRNA in English 1444 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0903203794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Madrid, March 9, IRNA -- Iranian ambassador to 
Madrid, Bahram Qasemi, and Spanish minister of industry and 
energy, Juan Manuel Eguiagaray, here today discussed ways of 
expanding Tehran-Madrid bilateral cooperation. 
  Qasemi briefed Eguiagaray on the present process of 
bilateral 
cooperation in the areas of energy and industry and voiced 
Islamic Republic of Iran's readiness to boost cooperation in the 
areas of vehicle manufacturing, ship building, aviation and 
power plants. 
  Eguiagaray in return referred to the importance of Iran and 
the "fruitful" bilateral cooperation in the past and said his 
country was for promotion of mutual cooperation. 
  He said Spain is to send an expert delegation to survey ways 
of improving bilateral industrial cooperation, Madrid's 
contribution to implementation of industrial projects and 
assisting Iran with its reconstruction projects during the 
second five-year economic developement plan. 
  The two sides also held talks on joint investment, and 
conducting of research by the two sides' experts in the field of 
industry, especially on car manufacturing, ship building and 
aviation. 

</TEXT>

