<H3> <TI>   New Israeli Ambassador Refuses To Assume Post </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0903204894 Helsinki Radio Finland in English 1930 GMT 9 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0903204894 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Radio Finland </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Arab lawyer named to the position of Israeli 
ambassador to Finland has refused to take up the post. In 
January the Israeli Ministry for Foreign Affairs appointed Yusuf 
Haji-Yahya as the country's ambassador in Helsinki but he has 
refused, citing personal reasons. Haji-Yahya, who has a law 
practice in Tel Aviv, says that he had made his decision already 
before the recent massacre of Palestinians at a mosque in 
Hebron. He would have been Israel's first Arab ambassador. 

</TEXT>

