<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Says New Phase of Proximity Talks `Serious' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0903214494 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1700 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0903214494 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Gustave Feissel, the UN secretary general's 
alternate special representative in Cyprus, submitted to 
President Glavkos Kliridhis a draft document from UN Secretary 
General Butrus Butrus-Ghali on the seven key points of the 
proximity talks agenda on confidence-building measures [CBM's]. 
Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said Kliridhis asked 
for time to study the draft document, and during talks tomorrow 
[10 March] and the following day he will raise a number of 
questions to clarify certain points. Kasoulidhis said the 
president will brief political leaders on the draft document 
during separate meetings tomorrow and the following day. 
  The spokesman said that the proximity talks are entering a 
serious phase. Asked whether he agrees with the evaluation of 
Robert Lamb, the U.S. State Department special coordinator on 
the Cyprus issue, that the CBM's are the first opportunity in 
decades to find a Cyprus solution, Kasoulidhis said it is a 
significant opportunity. The spokesman concluded by saying that 
the Cypriot Government is in daily contact with the Greek 
Government. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

